# Travel Discovery — Frontend Structure (strict)

Follow the project spec. **Never invent a different folder layout.**

## Top-level `src/` layout

```
src/
  api/           # Axios functions only (hotels.ts, auth.ts, …)
  assets/        # images/, icons/, logo/
  components/
    layout/      # Header, Footer, MainLayout
    common/      # Button, Card, Modal, Skeleton, ProtectedRoute, …
    forms/       # SearchBar, DatePicker, GuestPicker, …
  configs/       # antdTheme.ts, axios.ts
  i18n/          # en.json, hy.json, ru.json, index.ts
  pages/         # One folder per route/page
  router/        # Route definitions (index.tsx)
  store/         # Redux Toolkit slices + hooks
  types/         # Global shared types only
  utils/         # Global helpers only
```

## Per-page and per-component folder pattern

Every **page** (`src/pages/<PageName>/`) and every **major feature component** (`src/components/**/<Name>/`) MUST use:

| File | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `index.tsx` | Main React component (default export for pages) |
| `types.ts` | Component/page types (`type` aliases only) |
| `styles.module.css` | Scoped CSS — minimal, no animations |
| `const.ts` | Constants, i18n key names, enums |
| `utils.ts` | Optional — only when helpers are scoped to this folder |

**Do not** add `interface`, barrel `index.ts` re-exports, or extra files unless the spec requires them.

## TypeScript & i18n (mandatory)

- Use `type` aliases only — **never** `interface`
- **No** `any` — use `unknown` and narrow
- **No** `!` non-null assertions — use `?.` and guards
- Shared types → `src/types/`; page-specific → `pages/<Page>/types.ts`
- **No hardcoded UI strings** — all visible text via `useTranslation()` / `t()`
- i18n keys referenced from `const.ts` when page-specific

## UI & state

- Prefer **Ant Design** components; custom CSS only when AntD is insufficient
- **React Query** for server/async data; **Redux** only for global app state (auth, search, booking)
- One component per file; lazy-load pages with `React.lazy` + `Suspense`
- CSS Modules for scoped styles; theme via `ConfigProvider` tokens — avoid hardcoded hex in CSS

## Creating new work

When adding a page (e.g. `HotelDetail`):

```
src/pages/HotelDetail/
  index.tsx
  types.ts
  styles.module.css
  const.ts
```

Register the route in `src/router/index.tsx`. Add translation keys to `en.json`, `hy.json`, and `ru.json`.

## Package manager

Use **pnpm** only (`pnpm install`, `pnpm dev`, `pnpm build`). Do not use npm or yarn. Add direct dependencies with `pnpm add <package>` when importing packages not already declared in `package.json` (pnpm does not hoist undeclared deps).
